ABN_FOLLOW_UP.name: ABN_FOLLOW_UP
ABN_FOLLOW_UP.description: This table stores the data related to the follow up done on an Advanced Beneficiary Notice (ABN).

columns.name: NOTE_CSN_ID
columns.description: The contact serial number (CSN) of the contact.

columns.name: NOTE_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the note (HNO) record that contains the Advance Beneficiary Notice (ABN) information.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE_REAL
columns.description: A unique contact date in decimal format. The integer portion of the number indicates the date of contact. The digits after the decimal distinguish different contacts on the same date and are unique for each contact on that date. For example, .00 is the first/only contact, .01 is the second contact, etc.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE
columns.description: The date of this contact in calendar format.

columns.name: CONTACT_NUM
columns.description: The number of this contact.

columns.name: CONTACT_SERIAL_NUM
columns.description: The contact serial number (CSN) of the contact.

columns.name: COSIGN_REQUIRED_C_NAME
columns.description: The cosign requirement for the current note contact.

columns.name: AUTH_LNKED_PROV_ID
columns.description: The author's linked provider record.

columns.name: ENTRY_INSTANT_DTTM
columns.description: UTC formatted instant of entry for a note.

columns.name: UPD_AUTHOR_INS_DTTM
columns.description: UTC instant of update by a specific user.

columns.name: SPEC_NOTE_TIME_DTTM
columns.description: The note's specified date paired with the specified time.

columns.name: NOTE_FILE_TIME_DTTM
columns.description: UTC formatted instant of when a note is filed.

columns.name: AUTHOR_PRVD_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Author's provider type on a specific contact.

columns.name: NOTE_STATUS_C_NAME
columns.description: The status of the note.

columns.name: UPDATE_USER_ID
columns.description: The id of the user who updated this contact of the note.

columns.name: UPDATE_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: TRN_DOC_AVAIL_STA_C_NAME
columns.description: The availability status of the transcription.

columns.name: TRN_DOC_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The document type of the transcription.

columns.name: SENSITIVE_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: Sensitive status of a note.

columns.name: AUTHOR_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID associated with the user who is the author of the note.

columns.name: AUTHOR_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: NOTE_FORMAT_C_NAME
columns.description: The format of the note text like Plain Text, Rich Text, HTML etc.

columns.name: UPD_BY_AUTH_DTTM
columns.description: The instant when the note is updated by the author.

columns.name: AUTH_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: The authentication status category number for this activity if this note is a transcription. This is also known as the completion status.

columns.name: UPD_AUT_LOCAL_DTTM
columns.description: Update by author instant in local format.

columns.name: ENT_INST_LOCAL_DTTM
columns.description: Note entry instant in local format.

columns.name: SPEC_TIME_LOC_DTTM
columns.description: Note specified instant in local format.

columns.name: NOT_FILETM_LOC_DTTM
columns.description: Note file time in local format.

columns.name: DOCUMENT_NAME
columns.description: Contains the name of the multi-part document.

columns.name: PRE_UCN_NOTE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: This virtual item is populated with a category value from the note type (I HNO 50) according to the following logic:   * if the note type (I HNO 50) is populated, use the value directly * if the note type (I HNO 50) is null and the note is not ambulatory, return null   * if the note type (I HNO 50) is null and the note has an ambulatory encounter context, obtain a category from the UCN note type (I HNO 34033) and map that value to an equivalent category from the note type (I HNO 50), if possible
entries: Home Health Face to Face Attestation
Home Health Plan of Care Header

columns.name: NOTE_SHARED_W_PAT_HX_YN
columns.description: Was this note contact marked as eligible for sharing with the patient when it was last saved?  Notes will only be displayed in MyChart if their most recent contact is marked for sharing. If you want to determine if a note is currently shared, use the NOTE_SHARED_W_PAT_YN column in the HNO_INFO table instead of this one.

columns.name: NOTE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Identifies what type of note this record is.

columns.name: IS_PRECHARTED_YN
columns.description: This indicates whether or not the note is currently a pre-charted note (in appointment encounter).

merged.name: NOTE_ENC_INFO
merged.description: This table contains information from overtime single-response items about General Use Notes (HNO) records. Contact creation logic for clinical notes is as follows: 1. If a note doesn't exist, a new note is created. This represents the first contact on that note. 2. If a revision is filed by the incoming transcription interface, a new contact is created on the note being revised regardless of note status.
